# Dev server handling

The user runs their own dev server (`yarn dev` / `npm run dev`), usually on
port 3000 in an existing terminal. Do NOT kill, restart, or interfere with it.

- Never run `kill`, `lsof -ti:3000 | xargs kill`, `pkill node`, or similar.
- Never start a competing dev server on the same port.
- To verify changes, just `curl` the already-running server (e.g.
  `curl -s http://localhost:3000/...`). Next.js hot-reloads source edits.
- A restart is only needed for env/config changes (e.g. `.env.local`,
  `next.config`). In that case, ASK the user to restart it themselves rather
  than killing their process.
- If the server appears down, ask before starting one.
